# Centralized File Structure

## Central Files

This project uses **centralized files** to eliminate code duplication:

### `quiz.js` (Root Directory)
- **Universal JavaScript engine** for all quiz instances
- Contains the `QuizApp` class with complete quiz functionality
- **All quiz directories reference this file** via `../../quiz.js`
- **Never create local `script.js` files** in quiz directories

### `fontawesome.css` (Root Directory)
- **Central FontAwesome icons** for all quiz instances
- Contains all essential icons using Unicode symbols
- **All quiz directories reference this file** via `../../fontawesome.css`
- **Never create local `fontawesome.css` files** in quiz directories

## File References

**In Quiz Directories:**
```html
<!-- Correct references -->
<script src="../../quiz.js"></script>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="../../fontawesome.css">
```

**Quiz-Specific Files (Keep Local):**
- `quiz.json` - Quiz data and questions
- `index.html` - Quiz-specific HTML structure
- `styles.css` - Quiz-specific styling
- `banner.png` - Quiz-specific banner image
- `[source].pdf` - Quiz-specific source documents

## Benefits

✅ **No Code Duplication**: Single source of truth for JavaScript and icons  
✅ **Easy Maintenance**: Bug fixes apply to all quizzes automatically  
✅ **Consistent Behavior**: All quizzes work identically  
✅ **Reduced File Size**: No redundant files across directories  
✅ **Better Caching**: Central files cached once for all quizzes  

## Development Rules

**When Creating New Quizzes:**
- Use `_template/copyme/` which already references central files
- Never copy `script.js` or `fontawesome.css` to quiz directories
- Always use relative paths: `../../quiz.js` and `../../fontawesome.css`

**When Modifying Quiz Logic:**
- Edit `quiz.js` in root directory
- Changes apply to ALL quizzes automatically
- Test multiple quiz instances after changes

**When Adding New Icons:**
- Add to `fontawesome.css` in root directory
- Available to ALL quizzes immediately
- Use Unicode symbols for better compatibility